 /X\ WRC FIA WORLD RALLY CHAMPIONSHIP 2017 (DOUBLE BLURAY)                 /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
 \X/ Now on Blu-ray for the first time ever.                               \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
 \X/ Ever get the feeling we're living in a new golden age of world        \X/
 /X\ rallying? We do.                                                      /X\
 \X/ Let's look at the evidence:                                           \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
 \X/ Talented drivers? They don't get much better than SΘbastien Ogier,    \X/
 /X\ but he's been pushed hard all season by Jari-Matti Latvala,           /X\
 \X/ Kris Meeke, Thierry Neuville, Ott TΣnak and, latterly, Esapekka Lappi \X/
 /X\ all of whom have taken round wins.                                    /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ Powerful, interesting cars? That's been the best thing about the 2017 /X\
 \X/ WRC season. With the new rules allowing much more powerful engines    \X/
 /X\ and better aerodynamics, speeds have increased and coincidentally     /X\
 \X/ everything looks even more spectacular than usual.                    \X/
 /X\ The amount of time the cars now spend in the air on some events is    /X\
 \X/ the best guide to just how fast the crews are travelling!             \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
 \X/ Great races? With six different winners at the time of writing the    \X/
 /X\ answer is a definitive æYes!' The iconic stages of the World's most   /X\
 \X/ famous rallies including Monte Carlo, Rallye Finland, Argentina and   \X/
 /X\ Sardinia have seen some classic encounters.                           /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ Brilliant review? Of course, and now available on two-disc Blu-ray    /X\
 \X/ for the first time ever. Filmed throughout in HD, the Blu-ray version \X/
 /X\ is the best way to fully appreciate the stunning detail, breathtaking /X\
 \X/ footage and occasionally terrifying moments.                          \X/
 /X\ Exclusive extra features include awesome full stage on-boards with    /X\
 \X/ World Champion Sebastian Ogier, Esapekka Lappi, Thierry Neuville,     \X/
 /X\ Ott Tanak and Elfyn Evans.                                            /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\ The ultimate review of some wonderful sport for your collection.      /X\
 \X/                                                                       \X/
 /X\                                                                       /X\
